WEBVTT

00:00.450 --> 00:03.835
Hey everybody, good morning and welcome to church.

00:03.915 --> 00:10.224
It is so good to be with you today, whether you are in the room or wherever you are joining us from.

00:10.244 --> 00:13.609
We're so thankful that you decided to be with us today.

00:13.629 --> 00:15.252
And hey, especially welcome to you.

00:15.292 --> 00:20.660
If this is your first time here, man, we are so thankful that you decided to join us today.

00:20.720 --> 00:27.730
You need to know that this is a place where you belong, a place where your story matters to us.

00:28.194 --> 00:29.376
And it matters to God.

00:29.416 --> 00:33.221
It takes a lot of courage to step into someplace new, and we're thankful that you did.

00:34.063 --> 00:35.325
And we're gonna do some singing together.

00:35.345 --> 00:44.178
And we sing, and we worship every single week, and we believe that something powerful happens when we do this because of who we are singing to.

00:44.738 --> 00:50.567
And today, we're singing to a God that is a God of hope, a God of love, a God of freedom.

00:50.968 --> 00:57.938
And when we worship together, we have an opportunity to receive the hope that is found in Jesus to be reminded of who

00:58.146 --> 01:00.878
is and what he has done for us.

01:00.898 --> 01:04.594
Sonambach is staying with us as we sing, as we worship together.

01:04.614 --> 01:05.317
Here we go.

01:05.357 --> 01:06.482
Good to be with you.

16:10.018 --> 16:11.279
We thank you for who you are.

16:11.319 --> 16:17.105
And Jesus, we declare that you are worthy.

16:17.145 --> 16:18.646
You are worthy of our praise.

16:18.666 --> 16:20.067
You are worthy of our worship.

16:20.107 --> 16:24.852
God, you are worthy of everything that we have to give.

16:28.075 --> 16:30.317
God, there is no one like you.

16:30.337 --> 16:31.778
There is none besides you.

16:31.818 --> 16:39.826
God, there is nothing that this world has to offer that could ever compare.

16:40.354 --> 16:48.923
to your goodness, your faithfulness, your grace, your unconditional love for us, no matter where we've been or what we've done.

16:48.963 --> 16:56.832
The mistakes that we've made, God, you see it all and still, you chose us, you chose the cross.

17:00.116 --> 17:01.137
How about a gift that is?

17:04.200 --> 17:09.586
Gotta pray that you would help us just live from that place that you would help us

17:11.458 --> 17:14.762
God, be reminded of who we are, of who you say that we are.

17:14.782 --> 17:18.547
God, that we would fix our eyes on you.

17:18.607 --> 17:28.760
God, I thank you for this time and this place where we get to come together and lift our voices.

17:32.464 --> 17:33.706
Jesus, you deserve it all.

17:35.408 --> 17:40.434
And so right now I ask that you be drawing near to us, that you would speak to us, you would open our hearts

17:42.434 --> 17:43.396
Jesus, we love you.

17:44.599 --> 17:48.326
I'm going to pray all of this in your powerful and precious name.

17:49.148 --> 17:50.651
Amen.

17:50.671 --> 17:51.072
Amen.

17:51.092 --> 17:52.715
Church, it's great to sing together.

17:52.735 --> 17:59.730
You can go ahead and take a seat.

18:55.170 --> 18:57.353
Well, hey, everyone, and welcome to Eaglebrook Online.

18:57.473 --> 19:03.883
And as you just saw in that video, baptisms are happening next week, which is easily one of the best weekends of the year.

19:04.244 --> 19:06.226
But for us, we are switching it up this year.

19:06.246 --> 19:12.896
See, in years past, we would invite our online attenders to travel here to Minnesota in the middle of winter to get baptized.

19:13.037 --> 19:23.292
And naturally, no one would show up, but we would do the same thing in the summer and have over 70 people travel here from all over the US and even internationally.

19:23.352 --> 19:24.754
And so we decided,

19:24.834 --> 19:28.295
We would do our online baptism somewhere a bit more balmy.

19:28.677 --> 19:31.474
We have three viewing groups in southwest Florida.

19:31.938 --> 19:42.656
near the Fort Myers area and we have steadily been growing and we're going to join two of them for their services on Sunday and then we're going to head to the ocean to do our own baptism service there.

19:43.056 --> 19:58.802
Now we announced this last weekend and since then I've heard some grumblings from other staff and attenders at Eaglebrook saying things like the online team just wants to go to Florida to escape the cold and I'm sure you're going there for baptisms and I just want you to know

19:59.010 --> 20:02.280
that I'm personally offended by any attacks on my character.

20:02.300 --> 20:09.202
And if you think that I would try to leverage this situation for my own personal benefit, then...

20:10.210 --> 20:14.554
Well, all that to say, we are super pumped for what God is doing in Southwest Florida.

20:14.574 --> 20:21.381
And for Easter last year, they rented out a movie theater and they had all of their groups combined and had 115 people attend.

20:21.641 --> 20:28.769
We already have more people signed up to get baptized there than we have the last few years of online winter baptisms combined.

20:29.209 --> 20:31.011
It is going to be amazing.

20:31.051 --> 20:38.098
So if you wanna get baptized in Florida or if you wanna come hang out with us, shoot us an email at online at eaglebrookchurch.com.

20:38.466 --> 20:42.892
Okay, now I want to talk to those of you who live within travel distance to a campus.

20:43.173 --> 20:47.439
And I want to be as serious as I can in swim trunks and flip flops in the freezing cold.

20:48.100 --> 20:54.068
If you have put your faith in Jesus, but haven't yet taken this step to be baptized, now is the time.

20:54.529 --> 21:06.226
I have heard so many people who are just waiting for perfect circumstances or to break that addiction or to clean up their lives before taking this step and let me just say, theologically, that's out of order.

21:06.306 --> 21:11.536
Baptism is the first step of obedience after putting faith in Jesus.

21:11.756 --> 21:13.299
There is no prerequisite.

21:13.620 --> 21:18.789
If you have put your faith in Jesus, whether it was days or decades ago, now is your time.

21:19.070 --> 21:24.379
To get all the details and to register, head to egobrookchurch.com slash baptism.

21:24.419 --> 21:30.130
And as you're doing that, I'm gonna go warm up and hand it over to Jason for today's message.

22:15.458 --> 22:16.679
We are starting a new series today.

22:16.739 --> 22:18.201
It's called Our One Job.

22:18.502 --> 22:21.645
And there is a meme that says, you had one job.

22:22.306 --> 22:25.590
I don't know if you've seen these, but it's like people who just messed up the one job that they had.

22:25.610 --> 22:26.951
Let me show you a couple of examples.

22:30.275 --> 22:31.737
Come on, you had one job.

22:31.797 --> 22:34.280
Just put the cheese in the sandwich.

22:34.320 --> 22:35.281
Here's another one here.

22:35.301 --> 22:39.606
I think that one's real.

22:39.646 --> 22:41.408
I don't think anybody messed up on that one.

22:41.709 --> 22:42.930
Here's the next one here.

22:44.642 --> 22:46.724
of all the words that you're gonna misspell.

22:46.784 --> 22:48.726
Don't misspell the word school.

22:48.826 --> 22:50.128
And then here's a final one.

22:50.148 --> 22:54.832
There's a lot of confusion on that one.

22:54.892 --> 22:55.613
It's like, well, I don't know.

22:55.633 --> 22:56.434
Am I supposed to go left?

22:56.454 --> 22:57.355
Am I supposed to go right?

22:57.415 --> 22:59.797
You had one job.

23:00.158 --> 23:04.682
This is like when my wife got sick and she sent me to the grocery store to get some bone broth.

23:05.363 --> 23:07.465
And I came home a little bit later, no bone broth.

23:08.186 --> 23:09.047
And I had a couple of steaks.

23:10.308 --> 23:12.050
I had one job.

23:12.578 --> 23:15.442
There's about 1,700 commands in the Bible.

23:15.963 --> 23:22.232
But I want to make the argument today that while there's 1,700 commands in the Bible as a follower of Christ, we have one job.

23:23.233 --> 23:26.358
And that one job is called the Great Commission.

23:27.159 --> 23:34.610
But what concerns me is there was a recent study done by the Barna Research Group, and they found that 51% of churchgoers

23:35.362 --> 23:36.964
So we're not talking about the general population.

23:36.984 --> 23:39.206
We're just talking about people who attend church.

23:39.226 --> 23:44.090
51% of churchgoers had no idea what the Great Commission was.

23:45.692 --> 23:53.339
Of those who did know what the Great Commission was, about 25% were like, yeah, I've heard of it, but I'm not exactly sure what that means.

23:54.160 --> 23:56.762
And you might be sitting here and you're like, I don't really know what the Great Commission is.

23:57.743 --> 23:58.704
And my life's fine.

24:00.246 --> 24:02.007
Do I need to know what the Great Commission is?

24:02.067 --> 24:04.850
Why would that even be important?

24:05.282 --> 24:11.491
Imagine for a moment that your boss, CEO, someone like that, called you on the phone and said, hey, I have one job for you.

24:12.312 --> 24:13.454
I have this important job.

24:13.514 --> 24:15.056
I want you to do it.

24:15.277 --> 24:18.181
And you're listening to this on the phone and you go, my life's fine the way it is.

24:18.241 --> 24:19.183
Hang up.

24:20.765 --> 24:22.427
Probably not going to do that to your boss.

24:22.708 --> 24:25.392
Probably not going to do that to someone that you respect.

24:26.293 --> 24:28.136
We're not talking about your boss right now.

24:28.196 --> 24:29.618
We're talking about God.

24:30.402 --> 24:35.792
the one who holds the universe in his hands, the ones who created you and who loves you.

24:35.832 --> 24:40.881
If we're not doing the one job that he's called us to do, then what is it that we're doing?

24:41.943 --> 24:54.546
I was listening to another pastor and he said that when he was 16 years old, somebody asked him this question, if you could accomplish something with your life and you knew that God was with you and you wouldn't fail, what would you try to accomplish?

24:55.874 --> 24:58.237
That's a great question for if you're a younger person.

24:58.257 --> 25:03.644
What would you try to accomplish with your life if you knew that God was with you and that you would not fail?

25:03.664 --> 25:07.128
He said, I've spent the rest of my life trying to live out the answer to that question.

25:08.630 --> 25:15.139
It doesn't matter if you're 16 years old or if you're 75 years old, God has given to you a mission.

25:16.120 --> 25:17.842
The mission is the great commission.

25:18.882 --> 25:21.945
The great commission that I keep speaking about is the words of Jesus.

25:21.985 --> 25:26.831
These were spoken by Jesus himself, and they're recorded at the end of Matthew's gospel.

25:27.532 --> 25:28.233
Here's what it says.

25:29.254 --> 25:35.180
It says, then the 11 disciples, if you're paying attention, there's 12 disciples, why is there 11?

25:35.200 --> 25:40.346
Well, this is after Jesus' resurrection, and so Judas is no longer with them.

25:40.366 --> 25:44.651
Then the 11 disciples went to Galilee, the mountain where Jesus had told them to go.

25:44.671 --> 25:47.314
So Jesus says, hey, I'm gonna meet me here.

25:48.002 --> 25:50.826
When they saw him, so again, this is in resurrected form.

25:50.846 --> 25:52.649
So he died, he's now come back to life.

25:52.969 --> 25:55.012
Some of them worshiped him, some doubted.

25:57.015 --> 25:59.419
It's interesting that Matthew includes that note that some doubted.

25:59.439 --> 26:00.441
I'm like, who are the ones that doubted?

26:01.422 --> 26:05.388
Who are the ones who were like, I saw that guy die and now he's alive and I'm not sure, man.

26:06.810 --> 26:07.591
But here's what he says.

26:07.631 --> 26:09.194
He says they worshiped him, but some doubted.

26:09.514 --> 26:14.422
Then Jesus came to them and said, all authority and heaven and on earth has been given to me.

26:15.263 --> 26:17.426
And then here's the great commission, go.

26:18.626 --> 26:28.738
Go and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit and teaching them to obey everything I have commanded you.

26:29.819 --> 26:38.349
And then Jesus adds these words, and surely I am with you always to the very end of the age.

26:38.369 --> 26:42.354
If we miss this one verse in the Bible, you might just waste your life.

26:44.034 --> 26:46.998
The one life that God has given to you, you might waste your life.

26:47.218 --> 26:50.342
You're gonna find something, but you might miss the one thing.

26:51.484 --> 27:03.099
You're gonna find something to occupy your time and occupy your mind, and you're gonna get busy doing something, and you might miss out on the one mission, the one job that Jesus Christ has for all of his followers.

27:03.920 --> 27:07.404
So we're gonna take the next three weeks, and we're gonna teach through this one verse.

27:07.705 --> 27:09.147
Today I wanna start with the word go.

27:10.829 --> 27:11.730
Jesus says go.

27:12.802 --> 27:16.227
make disciples of all nations.

27:16.247 --> 27:18.310
When was the last time you shared your faith with someone?

27:20.634 --> 27:30.028
When is the last time you were talking to someone, they didn't really know God, they didn't really know Jesus, they didn't understand what it means to be a follower of Christ, and you sat down and you tried to explain to them what that means.

27:30.469 --> 27:31.751
When was the last time that you did that?

27:33.674 --> 27:36.498
I asked myself that question this fall, I was embarrassed.

27:38.210 --> 27:47.622
Outside of speaking and sharing my faith that way, I could not remember in my everyday life the last time I had told someone about Jesus Christ.

27:47.642 --> 27:54.150
I work at a church, I'm around Christians, I'm friends with Christians, my kids go to a Christian school, I wouldn't have it any differently, but here's what that means.

27:54.470 --> 27:56.693
That means I have to go.

27:57.854 --> 28:02.580
My wife Sarah and I were at a restaurant recently in Minneapolis and the waitress happened to ask us, she said, where are you guys from?

28:02.640 --> 28:04.142
And we said, oh, we're from Ham Lake.

28:05.324 --> 28:07.346
Pretty sure she had no idea where that was.

28:08.002 --> 28:09.645
And so she went to ring up our bill.

28:09.705 --> 28:13.512
And as she was doing that, I just, I had this thought that I attribute to the Holy Spirit.

28:13.973 --> 28:15.876
And it was, why don't you invite her to church?

28:17.038 --> 28:18.902
She's already asking you questions about yourself.

28:18.922 --> 28:21.627
Why don't you ask her a question and then invite her to church?

28:22.488 --> 28:24.392
And so she came back and I said, well, where do you live?

28:24.412 --> 28:27.718
And she said, I live in Minneapolis and started kind of telling us a little bit about that.

28:27.738 --> 28:28.580
And I said, oh, you know what?

28:28.600 --> 28:29.662
I'm a pastor of the church.

28:30.363 --> 28:32.146
We have a campus in Minneapolis.

28:32.770 --> 28:33.671
It's called Eagle Brook.

28:33.691 --> 28:34.972
She said, oh, I've seen the signs.

28:35.032 --> 28:36.834
Isn't that off 11th Street in Hennepin?

28:36.854 --> 28:37.895
I said, yeah, that's the one.

28:39.237 --> 28:41.379
I started talking about what I love about our church.

28:41.439 --> 28:42.560
And at the end, she goes, you know what?

28:42.580 --> 28:43.521
I think I'm gonna come.

28:45.123 --> 28:47.926
I was at a dinner recently with some Eagle Brook families.

28:48.046 --> 28:49.688
And I was talking to a guy, he's a football coach.

28:50.689 --> 28:55.414
He said, I think I've gotten eight or nine of my guys to come to church.

28:55.434 --> 28:56.595
I said, you're not a football coach.

28:56.916 --> 28:59.058
You are an ambassador of Christ.

29:00.098 --> 29:05.746
Same night, I was talking to a woman who works as a nurse in the cancer treatment area of Mayo Clinic.

29:07.168 --> 29:08.290
I said, you're not just a nurse.

29:08.871 --> 29:11.735
You are the hands and feet of Jesus.

29:11.755 --> 29:16.061
You are loving people and caring for people in some of their hardest moments of life.

29:17.063 --> 29:21.850
I was talking to another woman who leads a Bible study for middle school girls out of her house.

29:23.352 --> 29:24.914
Do you see your life that way?

29:25.922 --> 29:30.947
Do you see yourself as having a ministry as being on a mission?

29:31.868 --> 29:36.633
In Luke chapter 15, Jesus tells three stories and in all of them, something has been lost.

29:37.374 --> 29:44.101
So there's a lost sheep, a lost coin, a lost son and in each of the stories, what's been lost matters to someone.

29:45.082 --> 29:53.170
So the sheep matters to the shepherd and the coin matters to the woman who is poor and the son matters to the father.

29:53.922 --> 29:57.867
My wife, Sarah and I, we have five kids, so there's a higher probability we're gonna lose one.

29:59.129 --> 30:01.512
Don't judge, but there's just a higher property, or you're gonna lose one of your kids.

30:02.393 --> 30:10.324
We were at the old holodazzle parade in downtown Minneapolis, this was years ago, and when the parade was over, everybody's just racing to get to their car, beat traffic, and so I'm the same.

30:10.344 --> 30:12.206
We're going through Macy's department store.

30:12.487 --> 30:14.009
I'm like, okay, come on, we gotta go, go, go.

30:14.569 --> 30:20.978
My daughter Isabel, who was three years old at the time, all of a sudden she goes, I gotta go to the bathroom.

30:21.986 --> 30:24.329
And I'm like, you've got to be kidding me.

30:24.349 --> 30:27.393
We got snow pants and hats and mittens and boots.

30:27.414 --> 30:29.577
So I said to Sarah, I said, hey, you stay here with the boys.

30:30.177 --> 30:32.541
I'll go take Isabelle to the bathroom.

30:32.561 --> 30:33.121
We got done.

30:33.161 --> 30:38.769
We were walking back to meet Sarah and I looked over to my right and there was no Isabelle.

30:40.151 --> 30:41.834
And so I start calling out her name.

30:42.715 --> 30:44.597
I start retracing my steps.

30:44.818 --> 30:46.860
I am in a full on panic at this point.

30:47.461 --> 30:50.866
I mean, I'm imagining going up to Sarah and going, I lost our daughter.

30:52.258 --> 30:54.401
department store in Minneapolis, you know, we're going about it.

30:54.961 --> 30:56.343
I mean, I am panicking.

30:57.444 --> 31:04.273
Just then I looked over and I saw a blonde ponytail poking out of a coat rack.

31:04.293 --> 31:08.178
She had been playing hide and seek and thought that was really funny.

31:09.760 --> 31:10.741
I didn't think it was very funny.

31:11.682 --> 31:13.885
And so I went over and I kind of peeled the coats back.

31:13.965 --> 31:18.130
I looked her in the eyes and I said, let's not tell your mom about this.

31:20.226 --> 31:22.931
When you lose something that's valuable for you, what do you do?

31:22.971 --> 31:23.893
You go search for it.

31:24.714 --> 31:26.999
At no point did I think to myself, you know what?

31:27.840 --> 31:28.341
She'll turn up.

31:30.285 --> 31:33.691
And somebody will call us tomorrow, you know, we'll come back and get her.

31:33.752 --> 31:38.981
I mean, I never once thought that because when you lose something that's valuable to you, what do you do?

31:39.122 --> 31:41.426
You drop everything, you go searching for it.

31:42.690 --> 31:46.534
In Luke 15, Jesus says, here's what God would drop everything for.

31:46.854 --> 31:48.455
Here's what he would go searching for.

31:48.756 --> 31:50.137
It's a lost person.

31:52.279 --> 31:57.184
And when one lost person, one person who is spiritually lost comes to Christ.

31:57.204 --> 32:02.269
It says that there is an all-out celebration in heaven.

32:02.289 --> 32:03.610
Here's what it says in verse seven.

32:05.472 --> 32:07.674
In the same way, heaven will be happier.

32:09.996 --> 32:12.338
Over one lost person who returns to God,

32:13.634 --> 32:17.539
than over 99 others who haven't strayed away.

32:18.620 --> 32:23.646
It's a man named Don Ritchie who lives in Australia and he lives next to a cliff as known as the Gap.

32:24.107 --> 32:26.490
And here's a picture of what the Gap looks like, it's beautiful.

32:27.171 --> 32:33.639
But it's a really steep cliff and at some point along the way it became known as a place where people would go to take their own life.

32:34.940 --> 32:37.383
So people would jump off the cliff to their own demise.

32:38.525 --> 32:42.770
And Don Ritchie who's pictured here would live, he lived across the street.

32:44.066 --> 32:56.882
And he developed this practice that when he would see someone walking up on the cliff, the part where people would often jump, he would get out of his house, he would walk across the street, and he would yell out to them, can I help you?

32:56.942 --> 33:02.429
And then he would say, come on over to my house, we can talk and have some tea.

33:04.712 --> 33:12.562
As of 2009, Don Ritchie is credited with talking and preventing 180 people from taking their own life.

33:14.402 --> 33:17.006
He was given a medal of honor by the nation of Australia.

33:19.029 --> 33:25.458
When asked about his suicide prevention, Don Ritchie said this, he said, well, you can't just sit there and watch him.

33:32.308 --> 33:36.454
Every day, about 170,000 people die.

33:38.998 --> 33:42.002
And many of them are on what Jesus calls the wide road.

33:43.554 --> 33:45.837
It's a wide road that leads to destruction.

33:45.877 --> 33:49.761
It leads to separation from God for all of eternity.

33:49.981 --> 33:51.943
And we can't just sit there and watch them.

33:54.406 --> 33:57.750
Who is that person in your life who needs to hear about Christ?

33:59.532 --> 34:00.593
Could you pray for them?

34:00.633 --> 34:02.155
Could you tell them about Jesus?

34:02.195 --> 34:03.716
Could you invite them to church?

34:05.118 --> 34:08.882
In three weeks, we're starting a new series called Encounters with Jesus.

34:09.858 --> 34:11.841
We've been working on this series for several months.

34:11.881 --> 34:14.926
It's through the Gospel of Mark, and here's our prayer for this series.

34:15.827 --> 34:18.412
That people wouldn't just know about Jesus, but they would know Him.

34:20.555 --> 34:24.581
That people wouldn't just hear about Jesus, but that they would have an encounter with Jesus.

34:25.643 --> 34:29.008
Week one of that series is, will you follow Jesus?

34:30.591 --> 34:32.434
It's the perfect message to invite someone to.

34:32.834 --> 34:35.218
Who needs to hear that message in your life?

34:35.938 --> 34:44.654
Who is that person that you're praying for that you're talking to that you could invite to hear that message and to hear the news of what Jesus wants to do in that person's life?

34:46.358 --> 34:48.482
Why does our church care so much for lost people?

34:48.522 --> 34:49.103
Here's two reasons.

34:49.123 --> 34:51.047
The first one, heaven and hell are real.

34:53.972 --> 34:56.136
We don't often think about this, but heaven and hell are real.

34:57.238 --> 34:59.282
It was reading through a book in the New Testament called Jude.

35:00.322 --> 35:03.545
And Jude, the author has some kind of bullet point quick things for Christians.

35:03.586 --> 35:05.948
And he says, keep yourself in the love of God.

35:06.188 --> 35:07.229
And then he writes these words.

35:08.891 --> 35:11.955
He says, save others by snatching them from the fire.

35:15.599 --> 35:18.001
And I read that verse and I just stared at it.

35:20.904 --> 35:22.947
What does it mean to snatch someone from the fire?

35:22.967 --> 35:23.847
How do you do that?

35:25.549 --> 35:27.271
And so I started studying this verse.

35:27.291 --> 35:29.874
And the way you do that is to share the gospel.

35:30.850 --> 35:32.131
We don't save people.

35:32.251 --> 35:33.172
God saves people.

35:33.432 --> 35:37.336
And the way that he's done that is through the good news of what Christ did on the cross for them.

35:38.417 --> 35:47.125
When you start telling people about Jesus and what he did and the gospel, that's how you saved someone and snatched someone from the fire.

35:47.145 --> 35:53.712
That's why the book of Romans says how beautiful are the feet of those who bring the good news.

35:54.753 --> 36:00.498
There's a man named Wells Crowther who worked for a stock company that was based at the World Trade Center South Towers.

36:00.994 --> 36:02.296
and he was there on 9-11.

36:02.316 --> 36:05.381
He was working on the 77th floor.

36:06.923 --> 36:09.648
At 9-03, a plane crashed into the tower.

36:11.991 --> 36:15.076
At 9-12, he called his mom to tell her that he was okay.

36:17.199 --> 36:24.050
He then went from the 77th floor down to the 76th floor in the lobby, and there were 17 people who were injured.

36:25.762 --> 36:32.371
One of them, a woman named Lucy was badly burned, and so when Wells wasn't a stock trader, he was a volunteer firefighter.

36:33.933 --> 36:39.540
He scooped up Lucy, he said to the other 16, follow me, and he led them down the stairwell to safety.

36:41.282 --> 36:44.266
And then Wells Crowther did something that I don't think most of us would do.

36:46.269 --> 36:47.010
He ran back up.

36:50.034 --> 36:53.298
He had a red bandana in his backpack, he put it over his face,

36:54.114 --> 36:59.480
to breathe with all the smoke and the debris, and he ran back up to try to save more people.

37:01.403 --> 37:05.368
Afterwards, people would talk and they would say, who is that guy in the red bandana?

37:05.388 --> 37:07.410
We were all running down, he was running up.

37:09.853 --> 37:14.859
And people would report, you know, this guy in the red bandana picked me up and brought me down to safety, who is that person?

37:17.142 --> 37:20.786
Wells is credited with saving 18 people's lives that day.

37:23.202 --> 37:31.331
And then at 959, the tower collapsed while Wells was in the stairwell.

37:34.015 --> 37:34.775
He died a hero.

37:38.580 --> 37:41.724
Are you running away from lost people or are you running towards lost people?

37:44.247 --> 37:50.674
See, it's so easy to go, well, those people over there, like they're lost and all these things, I'm just gonna run away from them.

37:50.946 --> 37:52.348
I don't want to have anything to do with them.

37:52.408 --> 37:52.889
They're evil.

37:52.929 --> 37:54.372
We just got to be a get rid of them.

37:54.392 --> 37:58.118
Are you running away from lost people or are you running to lost people?

37:59.540 --> 38:03.347
Jude said you can save some by snatching them out of the fire.

38:03.407 --> 38:07.373
We don't work at the wells or at the trade center towers, like Wells Crowther did.

38:08.355 --> 38:17.490
But every day you go to work, every day you go to school, every day you're around people who spiritually speaking are lost and need to be rescued.

38:19.586 --> 38:20.687
Jesus said it this way.

38:20.727 --> 38:23.771
He said, I came to seek and to save the lost.

38:24.051 --> 38:25.773
That was Jesus' mission.

38:27.395 --> 38:28.957
And that is the mission he's given to the church.

38:30.418 --> 38:35.244
The great commission is the mission of every single follower of Christ.

38:36.626 --> 38:41.271
If you go to any number of churches, you might see many different things that you go, oh, that's what they care about the most.

38:42.352 --> 38:43.333
And then they're all good things.

38:43.353 --> 38:47.378
They're all things that you're like, yeah, that's important, it's good, but is it the most important?

38:49.378 --> 38:52.602
In his purest form, Jesus said, here is my mission.

38:52.942 --> 38:54.884
I came to this earth to do what?

38:55.125 --> 38:58.268
To seek and to save that which was lost.

39:00.431 --> 39:01.692
Who's that one person in your life?

39:03.595 --> 39:06.118
We share numbers after Christmas of how many people came.

39:06.138 --> 39:09.181
We had over 73,000 people attend in person this year.

39:09.241 --> 39:12.145
We talk about the over 600 people who gave their life to Christ.

39:12.205 --> 39:13.266
I get excited by that.

39:14.690 --> 39:20.899
But the reason why I get excited by that is not because it's a big number and not because it's a number, I get excited because it represents one.

39:22.482 --> 39:34.920
It represents one mom or dad and their son or daughter has been praying for them for years and they had a bad church experience and 40, 50 years later, they still reject God.

39:34.940 --> 39:41.650
And they came to church and God opened up their eyes and they believed

39:42.498 --> 39:46.583
and they received eternal life and their son and their daughter went home and they said, thank you God.

39:48.445 --> 39:56.595
It's one son, one daughter who drifts away from God and their parents are praying and they're on their knees begging God that their son or daughter would come home.

39:57.696 --> 40:04.984
And they come to church on Christmas and they hear the message of Jesus, they hear the gospel and God opens their eyes and they receive eternal life.

40:07.647 --> 40:09.810
And those parents are just crying and going, God, thank you.

40:12.354 --> 40:13.395
Thank you for hearing my prayer.

40:15.677 --> 40:20.903
It's one person who was spiritually lost who comes to know God who is found.

40:22.825 --> 40:23.846
Who's your one?

40:25.848 --> 40:30.653
Maybe another way of saying it is who is that person in your life who is the furthest from God but the closest to you?

40:32.094 --> 40:32.895
Who comes to mind?

40:32.915 --> 40:35.358
Who's the closest to you but they're the furthest from God?

40:35.598 --> 40:36.299
That's your one.

40:36.339 --> 40:39.602
That's the person to pray for, to talk to, to invite them.

40:40.866 --> 40:43.911
Now it strikes me before I leave this point, you might be someone else's one.

40:45.914 --> 40:50.681
You might be here today because there's a person in your life who loves you and cares for you and wants you to know God.

40:52.323 --> 40:53.785
The Bible says we are all going to die.

40:55.308 --> 40:57.471
And when you die, you will immediately face judgment.

40:58.633 --> 41:02.879
And you will either be judged for your life or what Jesus did on the cross for you.

41:04.041 --> 41:06.424
The Bible says the wages of sin is death.

41:06.464 --> 41:07.866
That's what we earn from our sin.

41:08.167 --> 41:10.290
It's death and separation from God.

41:11.234 --> 41:13.738
But the good news is that Jesus Christ offers you a gift.

41:15.321 --> 41:19.728
You just have to receive at His grace and His forgiveness into your life.

41:19.768 --> 41:24.456
The Bible says, if you'll confess with your lips and believe in your heart, you will be saved.

41:26.199 --> 41:28.643
Here's the second reason why our church cares so much about lost people.

41:28.663 --> 41:31.748
It says, the church is God's plan A.

41:33.350 --> 41:37.938
China has passed laws that effectively make telling people about Jesus illegal.

41:38.722 --> 41:41.528
You try to tell someone about Jesus, you could get arrested in China.

41:41.568 --> 41:44.774
You can't print Bibles, you can't print Christian books and materials.

41:45.155 --> 41:46.298
All of that's considered illegal.

41:47.219 --> 41:48.983
Now, when I hear stuff like that, I get angry.

41:50.226 --> 41:51.488
I think Jesus giggles.

41:53.011 --> 41:58.623
You want to know the fastest growing countries in the world when it comes to people becoming followers of Christ right now?

41:58.883 --> 42:00.146
It's China and Iran.

42:02.402 --> 42:04.465
That's where the most people are coming to faith.

42:04.525 --> 42:10.111
It is estimated that by the year 2050, there's going to be 100 million Christians in China.

42:11.173 --> 42:16.379
Many of them are young, educated, going to secret underground churches.

42:18.081 --> 42:25.911
In Iran, it is considered a national security threat if a person becomes a follower of Christ, and you can be punished with the harshest form of punishment.

42:27.292 --> 42:28.754
That's where the church is growing.

42:29.954 --> 42:35.061
Jesus said, I am going to build my church and the gates of hell will not prevail against it.

42:36.103 --> 42:38.286
You can pass all the laws you want.

42:38.486 --> 42:46.097
Jesus said, I am going to build my church all throughout history, people have tried to stop the church.

42:46.117 --> 42:55.730
New Testament, there was a man named Saul killing Christians, persecuting Christians, trying to stop the movement of Christianity and then on the road on the way to a city called Damascus.

42:56.802 --> 42:57.763
He has a vision.

42:58.064 --> 43:02.230
Jesus speaks to him and he changes his name from Saul to Paul.

43:03.973 --> 43:07.999
He becomes the Apostle Paul who brings the message of Jesus Christ all throughout the Mediterranean world.

43:09.361 --> 43:11.003
There's always been people trying to stop the church.

43:11.283 --> 43:14.929
Mao, Stalin, Nero, Emperor Caesar.

43:15.750 --> 43:17.813
Today we've named a salad after Caesar.

43:19.736 --> 43:21.358
And the name of Jesus reigns forever.

43:22.680 --> 43:26.546
He is the Lord of Lords and he is the King of Kings.

43:27.362 --> 43:32.350
We opened a campus in Plymouth this past fall, and it's just been unbelievable the stories that are coming out of there.

43:32.390 --> 43:35.334
We've had, on average, 3,000 people attend every weekend.

43:36.235 --> 43:37.658
And some of the stories are just amazing.

43:37.678 --> 43:40.362
There was one guy who lived in the neighborhood, didn't go to our church.

43:40.382 --> 43:43.186
He saw all the cars and people, and so he's not walking his dog.

43:44.168 --> 43:45.049
So he just stopped in.

43:45.109 --> 43:48.434
He handed the dog to one of our pastors, like, hey, can you hold my dog?

43:50.146 --> 43:53.631
And so here's one of our pastors, like the things you don't know you're going to do in seminary.

43:53.651 --> 43:54.793
He's just kind of sitting there with a dog.

43:55.274 --> 43:57.317
And the guy comes out and he goes, you know what?

43:57.337 --> 43:58.619
I think I'm going to come back.

43:59.941 --> 44:05.991
There was a young couple that had both lost their parents and they were hurting and they were looking for something.

44:07.433 --> 44:09.757
I started coming to church and as they walked out, they said, you know what?

44:09.777 --> 44:10.738
I think we found our church.

44:12.258 --> 44:16.444
I just got an email this week from a woman who had story after story from the Plymouth campus.

44:16.464 --> 44:26.659
She said her neighbor was a middle schooler, got invited by a friend, didn't go to church at all, started coming to ground zero, loves it so much that even when her friend doesn't come, she comes by herself now.

44:27.820 --> 44:33.849
There was another middle school student who started volunteering in our kids ministry, texted this woman and said, that was the best morning of my life.

44:35.492 --> 44:37.234
Experiencing the joy of serving God.

44:38.402 --> 44:43.249
One of their other neighbors had moved here from China, and they bought them a Bible, and we're starting to talk to them about Jesus.

44:43.289 --> 44:44.852
And this was all just in one email.

44:46.434 --> 44:47.175
That's the church.

44:48.197 --> 44:52.203
That's the mission that God has given every single follower of Christ.

44:52.263 --> 44:53.785
The church is God's plan A.

44:54.226 --> 44:59.974
One of my favorite stories in the history of our church happened the weekend that we opened up our Spring Lake Park campus.

45:00.655 --> 45:03.279
And we had previously been Spring Lake Park Baptist Church.

45:03.780 --> 45:05.863
They were kind of struggling a little bit, trying to figure out what to do.

45:05.883 --> 45:07.826
And so they voted to become an Eaglebrook campus.

45:08.418 --> 45:09.779
And not everybody was happy about that.

45:09.819 --> 45:11.221
There was people who left the church.

45:11.501 --> 45:14.163
There were people who were like, well, we'll check it out and kind of see how it goes.

45:15.104 --> 45:18.307
The weekend that we opened was a blizzard.

45:19.388 --> 45:20.449
We're like, nobody's gonna come.

45:21.230 --> 45:23.132
Like, why would I have a blizzard on this weekend?

45:23.192 --> 45:25.274
No one's gonna show up at how wrong we were.

45:26.635 --> 45:27.997
We had to set out extra chairs.

45:29.158 --> 45:33.402
We had to have staff members go out and try to help with parking, because the parking lot was full.

45:33.442 --> 45:34.823
We were parking people in the street.

45:35.123 --> 45:36.164
Somebody called the cops.

45:36.204 --> 45:38.066
I mean, the whole thing was just chaotic.

45:40.130 --> 45:46.817
And the whole time there was this 80-year-old woman who had been a part of the previous church, friendly part Baptist.

45:48.058 --> 45:50.961
She was standing on the street corner, the snow was coming down.

45:51.021 --> 45:55.725
And with tears in her eyes, she just said, look at what God is doing.

45:57.988 --> 46:00.810
She said, I've been praying for years that God would fill this building again.

46:00.870 --> 46:05.175
I've been praying for years that people would start coming to Christ and young people would start turning to God.

46:05.415 --> 46:08.658
And she stood there, tears in her eyes just going, look at what God is doing.

46:10.978 --> 46:13.681
The church is God's plan A.

46:15.062 --> 46:21.828
In 2024, there was a church in Red Wing, Minnesota, that reached out to us wondering if we would have interest in launching an Eaglebrook campus in their building.

46:21.848 --> 46:23.390
I want you to see the story of that church.

46:23.570 --> 46:23.930
Take a look.

46:35.061 --> 46:36.402
City of Red Wing is very unique.

46:36.622 --> 46:40.466
The downtown's so alive, a lot of businesses, a lot of restaurants.

46:40.834 --> 46:46.864
The Bluffs obviously are very beautiful because that small town feel where people get to know each other.

46:47.145 --> 46:50.330
And yeah, just such a friendly and welcoming town.

46:52.294 --> 46:53.376
My name is Bruce Jarman.

46:53.536 --> 46:55.720
I'm the campus pastor here at our Red Wing campus.

46:55.860 --> 46:59.506
I've been here since we opened last October, 2024.

47:07.106 --> 47:08.067
Hi, I'm Janie Fair.

47:08.147 --> 47:10.951
This is my husband Dave, and we've lived here about 20 years.

47:12.112 --> 47:16.417
So when we moved here in 2006, finding a church was super important to us.

47:16.457 --> 47:18.279
We wanted our kids to grow up in it.

47:18.299 --> 47:23.085
We wanted to be involved in serving, and so we tried a bunch of different churches, and Cornerstone was the one.

47:23.265 --> 47:30.354
We loved the preacher, we loved the people here, we loved kind of the focus and mission of being downtown, and to reach people for Christ.

47:31.138 --> 47:37.006
I think cornerstone always wanted just people to feel like they were loved and mattered and that we were gonna meet them where they were at.

47:38.609 --> 47:42.334
Cornerstone Church was a church that's been in this community for many years.

47:42.454 --> 47:53.550
Great church, great core group of people, about 80 people, but they were struggling to sustain it and to reach out to Eaglebrook and ask them what would it look like for them to become an Eaglebrook campus.

47:53.950 --> 47:56.814
And so that started a conversation about what that would look like.

47:56.975 --> 47:59.378
And there was excitement, I think, on both sides.

48:00.930 --> 48:07.297
I would say on all things, the Spirit of God has always been here in this congregation of following what God wants us to do.

48:07.617 --> 48:11.781
People praying, people praying for direction, and it just happened easily.

48:11.841 --> 48:15.325
Like the option came up for Eagle Brook in a different way of doing things.

48:15.445 --> 48:18.808
And I think people were excited for a new way of reaching people for Christ.

48:20.170 --> 48:24.915
For the most part, it was a smooth transition from Cornerstone to Eagle Brook.

48:25.135 --> 48:28.018
And from the day that we opened, we have felt

48:28.098 --> 48:30.262
accepted in this community.

48:30.663 --> 48:32.887
And opening weekend, we had 811 people.

48:34.269 --> 48:40.320
It was a sad time, but I think a lot of people saw that coming that, you know, it couldn't last forever.

48:40.921 --> 48:48.796
And I've been pleasantly amazed at how God has worked, you know, from transitioning us from Cornerstone to Eagleberg.

48:48.816 --> 48:52.402
It's encouraging because I think God was at every step of the way.

48:52.770 --> 48:55.615
For some reason, I believe that this was God's plan from the beginning.

48:55.835 --> 49:04.590
There seemed to be all these stories that linked us all together, and then you're like, that's why that happened, or that's why the Holy Spirit worked there, and so just was meant to be.

49:04.650 --> 49:09.458
I'm amazed because we see new people come in the doors every week.

49:09.698 --> 49:12.723
whether they've not been to church in a long time or maybe not at all.

49:13.164 --> 49:16.850
Our staff is hearing different stories that I've never seen a church like this.

49:17.151 --> 49:22.941
I've been apprehensive to attend church and I come in and I feel welcome and just the messages are right to me.

49:23.141 --> 49:27.829
And so we have seen new people come in every week and just hearing some amazing stories.

49:30.754 --> 49:35.442
My name is Lisa and I'm from Wanna Mango and I joined Eel Brooke about a year ago.

49:36.194 --> 49:41.861
I had received some pretty heartbreaking news and it was pretty much sink or swim for me.

49:41.881 --> 49:46.246
I was feeling broken spiritually, emotionally and physically.

49:47.287 --> 49:51.052
I just felt defeated and I didn't know where to turn.

49:51.072 --> 49:54.336
I was just really in a hurting place in my life.

49:55.657 --> 50:02.826
And I decided to start attending Eagle Brook here at the Red Wing campus and it was definitely a life-changing experience for me.

50:03.207 --> 50:05.049
And that is basically what saved me.

50:05.289 --> 50:06.130
It pulled me through.

50:08.002 --> 50:12.709
I have changed because I've learned that the mistakes I've made in my past, Jesus forgives us.

50:13.470 --> 50:14.812
He loves us unconditionally.

50:14.832 --> 50:17.336
I strive to be a better person now.

50:17.436 --> 50:18.858
I try not to judge others.

50:18.978 --> 50:22.463
I try to live a life that Christ would want to see me growing in.

50:23.205 --> 50:25.628
I've made a decision to dedicate my life to Jesus.

50:25.708 --> 50:28.012
I'll be getting baptized here in the church in three weeks.

50:28.633 --> 50:30.736
So that's been a really great decision.

50:30.916 --> 50:34.161
And it just gives me hope more than anything.

50:34.221 --> 50:34.962
It gives me hope.

50:36.706 --> 50:42.091
People need hope and people need a purpose and our purpose is in God.

50:43.112 --> 50:44.393
We were created to be with Him.

50:44.413 --> 50:53.261
So yeah, so the more people you can reach to bring people to God, that's what Jesus challenged us to do, go out and make disciples.

50:53.922 --> 50:54.663
That's our one job.

50:56.244 --> 50:59.988
I don't know how people get through life without having a relationship with Christ.

51:00.048 --> 51:01.850
So I don't know how they get through their work.

51:01.890 --> 51:06.674
I don't know how they get through illnesses and the hard things in life without having a faith in God.

51:07.074 --> 51:10.357
So again, that's why we need to bring people to Christ to help them with their lives.

51:12.459 --> 51:19.506
I believe if people had a church foundation of church family, there to support them, they would know that they're not going through life alone.

51:19.626 --> 51:24.250
And they'd learn that Jesus is there with you, no matter how alone you feel you are in this world.

51:24.310 --> 51:27.513
You have Jesus walking alongside you every step of the way.

51:28.074 --> 51:31.017
And that's why I think what Eaglebrook Church is doing is so important.

51:32.958 --> 51:36.722
I love the mission of our church, that we are laser focused

51:37.442 --> 51:39.325
to reach people for Jesus.

51:40.046 --> 51:42.190
And that never stops every week.

51:42.431 --> 51:43.793
We're seeing stories unfold.

51:43.813 --> 51:45.356
We're seeing lives transformed.

51:45.396 --> 51:49.923
And we see that all across all of our campuses, that we are reaching people for Jesus.

51:50.424 --> 51:52.127
And that is the most important thing that we could do.

51:52.207 --> 51:53.570
And I love that that is our mission.

51:58.057 --> 51:59.500
Got an email last year from someone.

51:59.520 --> 52:00.722
Yeah, go ahead.

52:05.090 --> 52:11.118
I got an email last year from someone who had been a part of the previous church, and he was saying that for three years in a row, they'd had to cancel their baptism service.

52:12.159 --> 52:14.362
Because they didn't have anybody who was wanting to baptize.

52:15.504 --> 52:23.013
And then last year, by the grace of God, we had over 20 people make a decision to get baptized and publicly declare their faith in Jesus Christ.

52:23.073 --> 52:26.658
And God is moving in that place in a powerful and new way.

52:27.499 --> 52:29.982
People ask me sometimes, why does Eaglebrook keep expanding?

52:30.002 --> 52:32.786
And I get the question, but I always think to myself, why not?

52:34.114 --> 52:38.160
Why not try to reach more people for Christ in this short time we have on this earth?

52:38.181 --> 52:41.586
Why not try to reach more people who are spiritually lost and bring them home?

52:41.626 --> 52:47.355
Why not be a part of what God is doing to restore marriages and families and lives?

52:47.455 --> 52:49.779
Why would we not want to do more of that?

52:50.721 --> 52:53.765
And so a better question than why do we keep expanding is what's next?

52:55.048 --> 52:59.394
And what's next is we want to be ready if another campus like Red Wing becomes a possibility for us.

52:59.415 --> 53:00.316
We want to be prepared for that.

53:00.596 --> 53:01.618
And here's how we can do that.

53:02.146 --> 53:05.249
When you give to our church online, there's two different drop-down boxes.

53:05.330 --> 53:06.451
One of them says general fund.

53:07.192 --> 53:09.154
And the general fund is how we do church.

53:09.174 --> 53:15.501
When you see thousands of students coming on Wednesday nights and worshiping God and giving their lives to Christ, you're a part of that.

53:16.302 --> 53:19.145
If you're someone who's giving and you're generous, you are a part of that.

53:19.165 --> 53:20.106
I hope you feel that.

53:20.867 --> 53:23.510
But there's also a drop-down box that says expansion fund.

53:24.251 --> 53:25.532
We created this several years ago.

53:25.572 --> 53:27.354
We said we want to have a mission.

53:27.394 --> 53:30.738
We want to use the resources we have to reach people for Christ.

53:31.266 --> 53:37.634
And so we created just that expansion fund that all that goes outside the walls of our church to reach new people.

53:38.295 --> 53:40.398
And so if you're someone who gives, I want to thank you for that.

53:40.418 --> 53:41.699
I want to thank you for your generosity.

53:42.601 --> 53:46.946
But I would also challenge you and urge you to be praying and saying, God, are you stirring something in my heart?

53:47.907 --> 53:50.851
Is there something in you going, man, I want to be a part of the mission of God.

53:50.871 --> 53:51.752
I don't want to just consume.

53:52.033 --> 53:52.974
I want to contribute.

53:53.254 --> 53:55.958
I want to be a part of the mission that God has to reach people.

53:57.460 --> 53:59.282
We can't just sit and watch them.

54:00.258 --> 54:04.483
As you came in today, you received this card, and there's a QR code if you're online.

54:04.523 --> 54:06.045
You can scan the QR code.

54:06.065 --> 54:09.168
There's also the web address on there where you can get to our expansion fund.

54:09.949 --> 54:11.371
But here's what I believe with all my heart.

54:11.451 --> 54:12.292
Jesus says, go.

54:13.393 --> 54:14.635
That is the mission he's given.

54:14.675 --> 54:22.664
The church, that is a mission he has given you in your life to go and make disciples, to snatch people out of the fire.

54:22.764 --> 54:25.307
We cannot just sit and watch them.

54:26.589 --> 54:27.890
So who is that person in your life?

54:29.442 --> 54:31.385
Who is that person that God is saying to you right now?

54:31.625 --> 54:31.826
Go.

54:33.088 --> 54:34.249
Let's pray together as we close.

54:39.978 --> 54:46.628
God, right now in this moment by your spirit, would you bring a name or a face to our mind?

54:50.234 --> 54:58.386
A name or a face of someone in our life that we know who needs you, God, who needs to hear about you, who needs to experience your love

55:00.546 --> 55:09.085
God, bring a name, bring a face to our mind right now in this moment, God, and I pray for the courage and I pray for the opportunity to talk to that person about Jesus.

55:10.508 --> 55:11.730
God, go before us right now.

55:11.810 --> 55:20.850
Prepare something in that person's heart that way they would be willing to receive and willing to listen, God, and I pray that you would go before us and that you would use us, God.

55:22.018 --> 55:35.917
that you would use every single person in this church, that no one would take a pass on this and kind of sit back up, but you would use every single person in this church to reach lost people, to share the message of the gospel that is life-changing for every single human being.

55:39.883 --> 55:50.898
God, I pray right now that we would go, that we would make disciples, that we would not just sit and watch, but that we would be part of the greatest rescue mission

55:50.978 --> 55:56.044
on planet earth, I thank you, God, that you seek and save the lost.

55:56.104 --> 55:58.087
You seek and save that which is lost.

55:58.788 --> 56:02.432
And God, I thank you because every one of us in this room at one point in our life was spiritually lost.

56:03.473 --> 56:04.315
And you found us, God.

56:04.335 --> 56:07.198
You left the 99 and you came for us as one.

56:07.498 --> 56:10.382
God, I pray that you would use us to be a part of that mission.

56:11.604 --> 56:12.565
We pray in Jesus' name.

56:13.446 --> 56:13.726
Amen.

56:14.447 --> 56:15.789
Hey, thanks for being here so much this week.

56:15.989 --> 56:16.850
We'll see you next weekend.

